    {
      "id": "anti-drift-htbh-numbers-tab-autogen-017",
      "added": "2026-05-15",
      "project": "htbh",
      "kind": "structural",
      "auto_safe": false,
      "priority": "P2",
      "status": "pending",
      "prompt": "HTBH Numbers tab in docs/GDD.html hand-encodes HP, cost, defense, worker counts, footprint for every v1 building. The .gd files in source/buildings/ are the actual truth. Today caught 3 rows drifted (Manor, House, Research Lab). Structural fix: add a build-time pre-processor to publish-gdd.ps1 that reads source/buildings/*.gd, extracts the @export and const values, and rewrites the Numbers tab rows. Same pattern applies to the Walls + Towers table and Units + Enemies stat tables.",
      "source": "2026-05-15 anti-drift analysis"
    },
    {
      "id": "anti-drift-yac-release-package-bump-018",
      "added": "2026-05-15",
      "project": "yac",
      "kind": "drift-fix",
      "auto_safe": false,
      "priority": "P3",
      "status": "pending",
      "prompt": "YaC has two version sources, CONTEXT.md and package.json. They drift because release.ps1 only touches CONTEXT.md. Add a step to release.ps1 (or push-to-github.ps1) that reads CONTEXT.md current version pill, parses X.Y.Z, runs pnpm version <ver> --no-git-tag-version so package.json moves in lockstep. The 2026-05-15 bump to 0.26.0 was hand-applied; future bumps should be automatic.",
      "source": "2026-05-15 anti-drift analysis"
    },
    {
      "id": "yae-artifact-session-path-hardcode-019",
      "added": "2026-05-15T20:00",
      "project": "yae",
      "kind": "structural",
      "auto_safe": false,
      "priority": "P1",
      "status": "pending",
      "prompt": "The cross-project-status artifact (Documents/Claude/Artifacts/cross-project-status/index.html) hardcodes the previous session VM mount root at lines 380-384 and 421: /sessions/keen-gifted-wright/mnt/. Each Cowork session gets a new mount root, so the live-refresh git + queue + audit panels silently fail on every new session and the dashboard falls back to the static snapshot. Fix: discover the mount root dynamically at refresh time. Simplest: ls -d /sessions/*/mnt/YesAndEverything 2>/dev/null | head -1, then substring-extract the session segment, then build all per-repo paths from that base. Apply to all five hardcoded path references in the artifact JS.",
      "source": "2026-05-15 queue-drain-frequent run, found while verifying item 014"
    },
